World Corporate Golf Challenge (WCGC), an International amateur golf event will make a big landing in Uyo, the Akwa Ibom state capital on June 4th when the second edition of Falcon Golf Development Company organized tournament tees-off in the state. Billed for the lush greens of Ibom Icon Hotels and Golf Resort, the 2021 edition of the tournament will feature over 60-teams battling for an all expense paid trip to the world finals of the competition in Cascais, Portugal in November. Already, all necessary arrangements at making sure that this year’s event goes as planned have been put in place. Speaking at a pre-tournament media chat in Lagos during the week, Chief Executive Officer of FGDC, Remi Olukoya said he expects a keen contest in Uyo, noting that the ultimate prize of this event is one that every team should vie for. “I am excited at the prospects of what we will see in Uyo this year. All the players coming are very competitive. So I expect a great outing”, Olukoya said. Dubbed ‘WCGC 2021’, several corporate organizations have registered to participate in the competition. They are Infinity Trust Mortgage, PricewaterhouseCoopers(Pwc), Citec Estate, Nigerian Liquefied Natural Gas (NLNG), and others. Apart from the array of prizes and tickets to be won, the ultimate prize for the overall winner in this year’s event a Benin handcrafted Claret bronze Jug.